  "original_title": "\u0da0\u0dd3\u0db1 - \u0d89\u0db1\u0dca\u0daf\u0dd3\u0dba \u0dad\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dcf\u0db4\u0dad\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dbb\u0dd4 \u0db8\u0dd4\u0dab \u0d9c\u0dd0\u0dc3\u0dd3\u0db8 \u0db8\u0d9c \u0dc4\u0dd0\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dcf\u0daf?",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Chinese-Indian ambassadors missed the meeting?",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Chinese Ambassador to Sri Lanka Mr. Chi Chenhon and the Indian High Commissioner Mr. Gopal Bagle were also scheduled to visit Kandy yesterday (27th), but the Indian High Commissioner suddenly canceled the visit.",
        "Mr. Chi Chenhon, the Chinese ambassador, was scheduled to visit the abbots of Malwatu Asgiri Maha Viharayan at 04.30 pm yesterday, and Indian High Commissioner Gopal Baglay was scheduled to visit the abbots of Malwatu Asgiri Maha Viharayan at 03.30 pm today.",
        "However, the Indian High Commissioner had suddenly taken steps to stop the journey. In this regard, during an inquiry from the Office of the Indian Deputy High Commissioner in Kandy, a spokesman said that due to the sudden illness of the Indian High Commissioner, his visit to Kandy was cancelled."
      ],
